<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<tt xml:lang="en-US"
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/ns/ttml"
  xmlns:ttm="http://www.w3.org/ns/ttml#metadata"
  xmlns:tts="http://www.w3.org/ns/ttml#styling">
  <head>
    <metadata xmlns:ttm="http://www.w3.org/ns/ttml#metadata">
      <ttm:title>437103532 - 1_bjy87ehu - PID 1530551</ttm:title>
    </metadata>
    <styling>
      <style xml:id="basic" tts:textAlign="center" />
    </styling>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div style="basic">
        <p begin="00:00:00.200" end="00:00:06.340" tts:direction="ltr">Hello, visitors. It is time to do your
<br />design challenge.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:06.340" end="00:00:10.820" tts:direction="ltr">Now, this is an opportunity for you to
<br />sharpen those design skills and add in</p>
        <p begin="00:00:10.820" end="00:00:14.520" tts:direction="ltr">those other skills that you've developed
<br />over this course</p>
        <p begin="00:00:14.520" end="00:00:18.860" tts:direction="ltr">and to apply them to create a better
<br />chart.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:18.860" end="00:00:23.780" tts:direction="ltr">Again, can you apply design principles for
<br />effective data communication?</p>
        <p begin="00:00:23.780" end="00:00:26.080" tts:direction="ltr">We've done several base camps already.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:26.080" end="00:00:28.560" tts:direction="ltr">You've learned about purpose, audience,
<br />credibility,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:28.560" end="00:00:30.900" tts:direction="ltr">and chart kinds, and you've been</p>
        <p begin="00:00:30.900" end="00:00:33.620" tts:direction="ltr">answering questions and building up your
<br />toolbox.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:33.620" end="00:00:37.340" tts:direction="ltr">Now we're ready to go for the design
<br />element.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:37.340" end="00:00:39.780" tts:direction="ltr">Now, remember, we're building our rubric
<br />and</p>
        <p begin="00:00:39.780" end="00:00:42.400" tts:direction="ltr">this rubric will be used for your final
<br />project</p>
        <p begin="00:00:42.400" end="00:00:48.320" tts:direction="ltr">and we need to ensure that we're being
<br />intentional about our design choices.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:48.320" end="00:00:52.700" tts:direction="ltr">I am looking at those three that I
<br />covered, layout, contrast,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:52.700" end="00:00:55.160" tts:direction="ltr">and gestalt principles, in addition to</p>
        <p begin="00:00:55.160" end="00:00:59.060" tts:direction="ltr">the PAC rubric that we've already built.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:59.060" end="00:01:01.160" tts:direction="ltr">What is the challenge prompt?</p>
        <p begin="00:01:01.160" end="00:01:03.060" tts:direction="ltr">I want you to think like</p>
        <p begin="00:01:03.060" end="00:01:05.965" tts:direction="ltr">a designer and you're going to make over a
<br />visualization.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:05.965" end="00:01:11.490" tts:direction="ltr">Going to apply what you've learned to
<br />hopefully improve what the chart has.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:11.490" end="00:01:16.250" tts:direction="ltr">You're going to create three visits or
<br />worksheets based on this exploration.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:16.250" end="00:01:21.150" tts:direction="ltr">The very first one, I want you to try your
<br />best at recreating the chart.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:21.150" end="00:01:25.430" tts:direction="ltr">Now, some of these charts might be very
<br />difficult to recreate tableau.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:25.430" end="00:01:27.655" tts:direction="ltr">I just want to see your best effort.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:27.655" end="00:01:31.720" tts:direction="ltr">Number two, I want you to create an
<br />alternative chart type.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:31.720" end="00:01:36.420" tts:direction="ltr">Maybe you have a bar chart and you are
<br />showing magnitude,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:36.420" end="00:01:40.020" tts:direction="ltr">but you may want to pivot to a stacked bar
<br />chart</p>
        <p begin="00:01:40.020" end="00:01:44.080" tts:direction="ltr">or maybe there is a chance to pivot</p>
        <p begin="00:01:44.080" end="00:01:47.720" tts:direction="ltr">all together and show a different field
<br />and maybe you want to do</p>
        <p begin="00:01:47.720" end="00:01:52.300" tts:direction="ltr">more of a an opportunity to show a
<br />relationship,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:52.300" end="00:01:54.100" tts:direction="ltr">so maybe you'll do a scatter plot.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:54.100" end="00:01:58.660" tts:direction="ltr">Really just push the envelope and see if
<br />you can apply a different chart type.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:58.660" end="00:02:01.280" tts:direction="ltr">Then finally, I want you to create a
<br />wildcard.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:01.280" end="00:02:05.220" tts:direction="ltr">Now, wild cards are your chances to be
<br />creative in my class.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:05.220" end="00:02:07.940" tts:direction="ltr">I want you to just push the envelope,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:07.940" end="00:02:11.220" tts:direction="ltr">maybe you learn from an outside resource,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:11.220" end="00:02:15.840" tts:direction="ltr">and I want you to apply at least three
<br />design principles.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:15.840" end="00:02:19.920" tts:direction="ltr">You should present your wildcard to your
<br />audience.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:19.920" end="00:02:25.250" tts:direction="ltr">That wild card could be your visualization
<br />number one or number two,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:25.250" end="00:02:29.070" tts:direction="ltr">you've just really supersized it to really
<br />apply those design principles.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:29.070" end="00:02:32.470" tts:direction="ltr">You're not focused on creating as much as
<br />you are designing.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:32.470" end="00:02:36.110" tts:direction="ltr">I want you to present that wild card to
<br />your audience,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:36.110" end="00:02:38.710" tts:direction="ltr">and you may have to be creative a little
<br />bit on</p>
        <p begin="00:02:38.710" end="00:02:41.510" tts:direction="ltr">your purpose and your audience. That's
<br />okay.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:41.510" end="00:02:48.010" tts:direction="ltr">I know that you can do that and be sure to
<br />address where your data comes from,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:48.010" end="00:02:50.160" tts:direction="ltr">that source, that credibility part.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:50.160" end="00:02:52.470" tts:direction="ltr">And I want you to follow that format where</p>
        <p begin="00:02:52.470" end="00:02:54.710" tts:direction="ltr">you're using the first two to 3 minutes
<br />where you'll</p>
        <p begin="00:02:54.710" end="00:02:59.410" tts:direction="ltr">address the audience and show that single
<br />wild card viz and insights,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:59.410" end="00:03:01.330" tts:direction="ltr">and then show the rest.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:01.330" end="00:03:02.730" tts:direction="ltr">Show that very first one,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:02.730" end="00:03:06.450" tts:direction="ltr">where you try to recreate it and that
<br />second alternative just so</p>
        <p begin="00:03:06.450" end="00:03:10.970" tts:direction="ltr">that we can see that you're exploring and
<br />working within Tableau.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:10.970" end="00:03:13.210" tts:direction="ltr">That is the challenge prompt.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:13.210" end="00:03:17.550" tts:direction="ltr">I hope that you are excited to make over a
<br />chart,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:17.550" end="00:03:21.450" tts:direction="ltr">and I can't wait to see your submission.
<br />Happy vizing</p>
    </div>
  </body>
</tt>
